PREPARATIONS for the Celebrity Soccer Games are underway. Last week, the teams and their players were announced. Team Gqom will play against Team Hip Hop. DJ Tira is the Gqom captain. His players include Andile Mpisane, Dladla Mshunqisi, Mampintsha and NaakMusiq. Big Zulu is the Hip Hop captain, whose players include Zakwe, Sjava, AKA, Kwesta, Donald, and Duncan. The second teams to play are Maskandi against Amapiano. Maskandi captain Khuzani “Khuba” Mpungose’s players include Ntencane, Tshatha, Smirnoff, Dumakahle, and Ngiga. Amapiano captain Kabza de Small’s players are Young Stunna, Mfundo Da DJ, SMS Mnono, and Hulumeni. ALSO READ: Baby joy for celebrity couple! Tira said: “Playing in the morning will give us an advantage. It means we will have enough time to prepare for the finals in the afternoon. I have DJ Cleo as my goalkeeper and Dladla Mshunqisi as my striker.” Soccer legends will also be part of these games. Khuzani said Siphiwe Tshabalala will be playing for Hip Hop, Siyabonga Sangweni for Gqom, and Phumudzo Manenzhe for Maskandi. The games take place on Sunday, 24 July at Wits University Sportsground. Gates open at 9am and tickets are available at Computicket. General tickets cost R150 and VIP R300.